#META# additionalLanguages: Old Uyghur (Old Uyghur script)
#META# documentType: Legal
#META# documentSubtype: Legal: Sale
#META# writingSupport: paper
#META# writingSupportDetails: Fading/discolouration :: fold lines
#META# writingSupportNotes: flat rotulus carefully folded into a narrow shape, written in discoloured ink that has reddened (with time)
#META# contentSummary: This is one of three Arabic land sale documents from Yarkand which Huart received from Pelliot to study. The original was accompanied by a modern transcription. This a land sale document dated Shawwāl 505/ April 1112 and concerns the purchase of an estate, including a manor house, vineyards and orchards for 700 dirhams, weighted against simple, pure, red gold.
#META# dates: The Gregorian calendar: April-May 1112 (1112-04-08 - 1112-05-06)
